'''''Deplanchea bancana''''' is a tree in the family [[Bignoniaceae]]. It is named for [[Sumatra|Sumatra's]] [[Bangka Island]].<ref name=TFSS/>

==Description==
''Deplanchea bancana'' grows up to {{convert|45|m|-1}} tall with a trunk diameter of up to {{convert|70|cm|0}}. The fissured bark is white to brown. The flowers are yellow and 5-lobed. The fruits are oblong and measure up to {{convert|14|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Distribution and habitat==
''Deplanchea bancana'' grows naturally in [[Sumatra]], [[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[Borneo]]. Its habitat is lowland forests from sea-level to {{convert|1000|m|-2}} altitude.<ref name=TFSS/>

